<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Basic_concepts">Basic conce=
pts</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracke=
t">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DP-value&=
amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D1" title=3D"Edit section: Basic concepts"><=
span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span><=
/div>
<p>In statistics, every conjecture concerning the unknown <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Probability_distribution" title=3D"Probability dist=
ribution">probability distribution</a> of a collection of random variables =
representing the observed data <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-ele=
ment-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" st=
yle=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" a=
lttext=3D"{\displaystyle X}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>X</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle X}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/68baa052181f707c662844a465bfeeb135e82bab" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:1.98ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle X}">=
</span> in some study is called a <i>statistical hypothesis</i>. If we stat=
e one hypothesis only and the aim of the statistical test is to see whether=
 this hypothesis is tenable, but not to investigate other specific hypothes=
es, then such a test is called a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/S=
tatistical_hypothesis_testing" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Statistical h=
ypothesis testing">null hypothesis test</a>.
</p><p>As our statistical hypothesis will, by definition, state some proper=
ty of the distribution, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Null_h=
ypothesis" title=3D"Null hypothesis">null hypothesis</a> is the default hyp=
othesis under which that property does not exist. The null hypothesis is ty=
pically that some parameter (such as a correlation or a difference between =
means) in the populations of interest is zero. Our hypothesis might specify=
 the probability distribution of <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-e=
lement-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" =
style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"=
 alttext=3D"{\displaystyle X}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>X</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle X}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/68baa052181f707c662844a465bfeeb135e82bab" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:1.98ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle X}">=
</span> precisely, or it might only specify that it belongs to some class o=
f distributions. Often, we reduce the data to a single numerical statistic,=
 e.g., <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><=
math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle=
 T}">
