        <mi>T</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle T}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/ec7200acd984a1d3a3d7dc455e262fbe54f7f6e0" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:1.636ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle T}"=
></span>, whose marginal probability distribution is closely connected to a=
 main question of interest in the study.
</p><p>The <i>p</i>-value is used in the context of null hypothesis testing=
 in order to quantify the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Statisti=
cal_significance" title=3D"Statistical significance">statistical significan=
ce</a> of a result, the result being the observed value of the chosen stati=
stic <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><=
math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle=
 T}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
