n></div>
<blockquote class=3D"templatequote"><p>The error that a practising statisti=
cian would consider the more important to avoid (which is a subjective judg=
ment) is called the error of the first kind. The first demand of the mathem=
atical theory is to deduce such test criteria as would ensure that the prob=
ability of committing an error of the first kind would equal (or approximat=
ely equal, or not exceed) a preassigned number =CE=B1, such as =CE=B1 =3D 0=
.05 or 0.01, etc. This number is called the level of significance.</p></blo=
ckquote><div class=3D"templatequotecite"><p style=3D"display: inline; paddi=
ng-left: 2.3em;">=E2=80=94=E2=80=8AJerzy Neyman, "The Emergence of Mathemat=
ical Statistics"<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Neyman1976_10-0" class=3D"reference"><a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/P-value#cite_note-Neyman1976-10"><sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>8<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup><span style=3D"display:none" data-plural=3D"1"></span></p></div>
<p>In a significance test, the null hypothesis <span class=3D"mwe-math-elem=
ent mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math=
-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/199=
8/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle H_{0}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>H</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle H_{0}}</annot=
ation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/43910602a221b7a4c373791f94793e3008622070" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:2.985ex; height:2.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle H_{=
0}}"></span> is rejected if the <i>p</i>-value is less than to a predefined=
 threshold value <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alpha" title=3D"A=
lpha"><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><=
math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle=
 \alpha }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
