    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \alpha }</ann=
otation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/b79333175c8b3f0840bfb4ec41b8072c83ea88d3" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:1.488ex; height:1.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \al=
pha }"></span></a>, which is referred to as the alpha level or <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Statistical_significance" title=3D"Statistical=
 significance">significance level</a>. <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-=
math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-=
a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/M=
athML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \alpha }">
  <semantics>
